<!doctype html>
<html>
 <head>  </head>
 <body>
 
  <form>
  <fieldset>
 
  <legend>Enter day you want to travel to Canberra: </legend>
  
  <input type="date" name="day"> </br></br>
  Number of days: <input type="number" name="numdays" min="1" max="7"> </br></br>
  Name: <input type="text">

  </fieldset>
  </form>
    
 </body>
</html>



notes: 
Fieldbox("fieldset") element: adds some nice styling to your forms and what it will do is 
it will actually draw a box around our entire form.
We can also put a caption inside of the fieldset element by using "legend" element.
